{"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"content","content":[{"anchor":"Overview","level":2,"type":"heading","text":"Overview"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"FlareUI"},{"type":"text","text":" provides an easy way to display different kinds of products with a single line of code. To display a set of products to the user, just pass a collection of identifiers to the "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/FlareUI\/documentation\/FlareUI\/ProductsView"},{"type":"text","text":"."}]},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift","code":["ProductsView(ids: [\"com.company.product_id_1\", \"com.company.product_id_2\"])"]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Once "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"ProductsView"},{"type":"text","text":" fetches these products from the App Store, it will display them to the user. If the products canâ€™t be fetched for any reason, the "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"ProductsView"},{"type":"text","text":" shows a message to the user that the App Store is not available."}]},{"style":"important","content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"By default, all Flare views use cached data if available; otherwise, they fetch the data. If you want to change this behavior, please read more about Flare configuration "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"link"},{"type":"text","text":"."}]}],"type":"aside","name":"Important"},{"anchor":"UIKit","level":2,"type":"heading","text":"UIKit"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"FlareUI"},{"type":"text","text":" package provides wrappers for the UIKit views. It can be easily integrated into UIKit environments using "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/FlareUI\/documentation\/FlareUI\/ProductsViewController"},{"type":"text","text":"."}]},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift","code":["let productsVC = Pro